This paper deals with the analysis of the Monte Carlo method for updating PageRank in a graph with edge arrivals, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient computation and storage of the PageRank values. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, the paper also discusses the application of PageRank in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI), as well as the use of random walks and probabilistic methods (cs.LG) and the analysis of worst-case running time (cs.NE).
